    <item>
      <title>How To Choose, Prepare and Store Asparagus</title>
      <link>https://beet.life/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 Apr 2016 14:51:39 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://beet.life/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;p&gt;We love asparagus! We try to incorporate it into the dishes we cook as much as we can.
It can be grilled, steamed, baked, sauteed, boiled and even microwaved! A medium spear that is
5 &lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;frasl;&lt;sub&gt;4&lt;/sub&gt; to 7 inches long is around 3 calories. It&amp;rsquo;s rich in vitamin K which helps prevent arteries
from hardening (a common factor in heart failure). It also helps build stronger bones.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;thick-or-thin&#34;&gt;Thick or Thin?&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What size you buy is a matter of preference. The thin ones are sweeter while the
thicker ones have a stronger asparagus flavor because it&amp;rsquo;s more mature. The thick ones are ideal
for roasting because they are more tender. Thin ones are ideal for soups because they contain less
fibrous material. The key is to look for firm stems with a bright green color.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;how-do-i-store-asparagus&#34;&gt;How do I store asparagus?&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do not wash before storing. Store in the refrigerator to keep fresh.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;how-do-i-prepare-asparagus-for-cooking-or-eating&#34;&gt;How do I prepare asparagus for cooking or eating?&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Preparing asparagus for cooking is very easy. There are two ways we like to use: &lt;em&gt;Peeling and Cutting&lt;/em&gt;. The bottom of an asparagus stalk can be very rough.&lt;/p&gt;

























&lt;img itemprop=&#34;image&#34; class=&#34;bl-img bl-img-margin lazyload&#34; src=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0019-full@1x.jpg&#34; data-srcset=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0019-mobile@1x.jpg 435w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0019-full@1x.jpg 533w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0019-mobile@2x.jpg 870w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0019-full@2x.jpg 1066w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0019-mobile@3x.jpg 1305w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0019-full@3x.jpg 1600w&#34; data-sizes=&#34;(max-width: 533px) 100vw, 533px&#34; alt=&#34;asparagus bottom&#34; srcset=&#34;data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==&#34;&gt;






&lt;p&gt;Cutting or peeling prevents stringiness when the asparagus is cooked. It also cuts down on cooking time. In our experience, cutting works best for thin asparagus while peeling works best for thick ones.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div itemscope itemtype=&#34;https://schema.org/Recipe&#34;&gt;
&lt;h1 itemprop=&#34;name&#34; class=&#34;mdl-typography--text-center bl-how-to-title&#34;&gt;Clean and Peel&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;bl-how-to-instructions&#34;&gt;Instructions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol itemprop=&#34;recipeInstructions&#34; itemscope itemtype=&#34;http://schema.org/ItemList&#34; content=&#34;http://schema.org/ItemListOrderAscending&#34; class=&#34;bl-recipe-steps&#34;&gt;

&lt;li itemprop=&#34;itemListElement&#34; class=&#34;bl-recipe-steps__step&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;After washing, use a vegetable peeler to peel the outer layer of the lower stem of the asparagus.&lt;/p&gt;



















&lt;img itemprop=&#34;image&#34; class=&#34;bl-img lazyload&#34; src=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0482-full@1x.jpg&#34; data-srcset=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0482-mobile@1x.jpg 435w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0482-mobile@2x.jpg 870w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0482-full@1x.jpg 876w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0482-mobile@3x.jpg 1305w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0482-full@2x.jpg 1752w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0482-full@3x.jpg 2628w&#34; data-sizes=&#34;(max-width: 876px) 100vw, 876px&#34; alt=&#34;Image demonstrating the previous recipe step instructions&#34; srcset=&#34;data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==&#34;&gt;


&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li itemprop=&#34;itemListElement&#34; class=&#34;bl-recipe-steps__step&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;When you&amp;rsquo;re done peeling, it should look like this:&lt;/p&gt;



















&lt;img itemprop=&#34;image&#34; class=&#34;bl-img lazyload&#34; src=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0487-full@1x.jpg&#34; data-srcset=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0487-mobile@1x.jpg 435w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0487-mobile@2x.jpg 870w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0487-full@1x.jpg 876w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0487-mobile@3x.jpg 1305w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0487-full@2x.jpg 1752w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160228-DSC_0487-full@3x.jpg 2628w&#34; data-sizes=&#34;(max-width: 876px) 100vw, 876px&#34; alt=&#34;Image demonstrating the previous recipe step instructions&#34; srcset=&#34;data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==&#34;&gt;


&lt;/li&gt;


&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div itemscope itemtype=&#34;https://schema.org/Recipe&#34;&gt;
&lt;h1 itemprop=&#34;name&#34; class=&#34;mdl-typography--text-center bl-how-to-title&#34;&gt;Clean and Cut&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;bl-how-to-instructions&#34;&gt;Instructions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol itemprop=&#34;recipeInstructions&#34; itemscope itemtype=&#34;http://schema.org/ItemList&#34; content=&#34;http://schema.org/ItemListOrderAscending&#34; class=&#34;bl-recipe-steps&#34;&gt;

&lt;li itemprop=&#34;itemListElement&#34; class=&#34;bl-recipe-steps__step&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;After washing, snap or cut off the dry ends of asparagus.&lt;/p&gt;



















&lt;img itemprop=&#34;image&#34; class=&#34;bl-img lazyload&#34; src=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0046-full@1x.jpg&#34; data-srcset=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0046-mobile@1x.jpg 435w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0046-mobile@2x.jpg 870w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0046-full@1x.jpg 876w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0046-mobile@3x.jpg 1305w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0046-full@2x.jpg 1752w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0046-full@3x.jpg 2628w&#34; data-sizes=&#34;(max-width: 876px) 100vw, 876px&#34; alt=&#34;Image demonstrating the previous recipe step instructions&#34; srcset=&#34;data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==&#34;&gt;


&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li itemprop=&#34;itemListElement&#34; class=&#34;bl-recipe-steps__step&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;When you&amp;rsquo;re done cutting or snapping off the dry ends, it should look like this:&lt;/p&gt;



















&lt;img itemprop=&#34;image&#34; class=&#34;bl-img lazyload&#34; src=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0026-full@1x.jpg&#34; data-srcset=&#34;https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0026-mobile@1x.jpg 435w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0026-full@1x.jpg 616w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0026-mobile@2x.jpg 870w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0026-full@2x.jpg 1233w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0026-mobile@3x.jpg 1305w, https://beet.life/images/articles/how-to-prep-asparagus/20160308-DSC_0026-full@3x.jpg 1849w&#34; data-sizes=&#34;(max-width: 616px) 100vw, 616px&#34; alt=&#34;Image demonstrating the previous recipe step instructions&#34; srcset=&#34;data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==&#34;&gt;


&lt;/li&gt;


&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After that, you&amp;rsquo;re good to go. Happy Cooking!&lt;/p&gt;

